remarks.format:
  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="a70c8-102">Oggetto `SpeechDetected` evento viene generato mediante il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> classi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a70c8-102">A `SpeechDetected` event is raised by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> classes.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a70c8-103">**SpeechDetected** gli eventi vengono generati quando un motore di riconoscimento può identificare l'input audio come funzione vocale risorse umane.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a70c8-103">**SpeechDetected** events are generated when a recognition engine can identify audio input as human speech.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a70c8-104"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechDetectedEventArgs> deriva da <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a70c8-104"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechDetectedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="a70c8-105">L'esempio seguente crea un gestore per <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> gli eventi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a70c8-105">The example below creates a handler for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a70c8-106">Il gestore inizializza un display ogni volta che il riconoscimento vocale viene rilevata e Visualizza informazioni sullo stato, tra cui la posizione audio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a70c8-106">The handler initializes a display every time speech is detected and displays status information, including audio position.</span></span>  
  
```  
_recognizer.SpeechDetected +=  
  delegate(object sender, SpeechDetectedEventArgs eventArgs)   
  {  
  
    // Clear previous recognition information.  
    _audioDeviceStatusLabel.Enabled = true;  
    _audioDeviceStatusLabel.Visible = true;  
    Utils.DisplayAudioInputFormat(_audioStateLabel, _recognizer);  
    Utils.DisplayRecognizerState(_recognizerStateLabel, _recognizer.State);  
    Utils.DisplaySpeechDetected(_speechDetectedLabel, eventArgs.AudioPosition);  
  };  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="a70c8-109">L'esempio seguente crea un gestore per <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> gli eventi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a70c8-109">The example below creates a handler for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechDetected?displayProperty=nameWithType> events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a70c8-110">Il gestore consente di inizializzare una visualizzazione vocale ogni ora viene rilevato e Visualizza informazioni sullo stato, tra cui la posizione audio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a70c8-110">The handler initializes a display each time speech is detected and displays status information, including audio position.</span></span>  
  
```  
_recognizer.SpeechDetected +=  
  delegate(object sender, SpeechDetectedEventArgs eventArgs)   
  {  
  
    // Clear previous recognition information.  
    _audioDeviceStatusLabel.Enabled = true;  
    _audioDeviceStatusLabel.Visible = true;  
    Utils.DisplayAudioInputFormat(_audioStateLabel, _recognizer);  
    Utils.DisplayRecognizerState(_recognizerStateLabel, _recognizer.State);  
    Utils.DisplaySpeechDetected(_speechDetectedLabel, eventArgs.AudioPosition);  
  };  
```
